              "src": "images/2016-01-14-15.01.06-1-768x1024.jpg",
              "alt": "2016-01-14 15.01.06-1",
              "title": null
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " After a delicious lunch, we had a fun visit with the restaurant owners and learned a neat fact: The restaurant owners are one of the few people who hold a key to the Abernethy Tower! The Abernethy Tower is one of only two round towers in the Irish style left in Scotland. It was a lot of fun to have the big brass key handed over to us and to climb up the spiral staircase to take in the view."
          }
